Package: memo
Type: Package
Title: In-memory caching of repeated computations, using pointer equivalence.
Version: 0.1
Date: 2015-4-25
Author: Peter Meilstrup <peter.meilstrup@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Peter Meilstrup <peter.meilstrup@gmail.com>
Description: This package implements a cache that can be used to avoid repeated
    computations of functions. The cache lookup is based on object identity (i.e.
    pointer equivalence) which is suited for functions like accessors, that are
    called repeatedly on the same object.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 0.2),
    knitr
Collate:
    'lru.R'
    'cache.R'
    'getPointer.R'
    'memo-description.r'
VignetteBuilder: knitr
